latestIgtvVideos.title: I Have #pcos And It’s OK !
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Today I’d like to talk to you about #pcosawareness . September is the month of #awareness for women all over the world living a #pcoslife .

1 out of 5 women in #india suffer from PCOS, this in many goes undiagnosed and they live a life with problems like #acne #obesity and even #infertility . 

I am a #pcosfighter who has faced hormonal, physical & emotional issues due to PCOS. But I stand tall today because I’m a #pcoswarrior . It’s time we women check ourselves and follow a #healthylifestyle, PCOS IS MANAGEABLE SO LETS DO THIS, talk about it.... get it diagnosed and follow the lifestyle changes to live a #healthyandhappy life, because #youarenotalone . 

I have joined hands with @ozivanutrition for the  #MyPCOSStory movement to spread awareness about PCOS and remove the hesitation that surrounds it. 
Our collective participation and support to this movement will encourage, empower and educate women about PCOS and how it can be managed by adopting healthy lifestyle changes and a clean plant-based diet.I have PCOS and it’s okay!

Let's come together and show our support. I nominate @supermom_mitali @trupti.marolia @drishtigwalani 

Show your support in 3 steps:
1. Post a picture of yourself in a blindfold 
2. Nominate 3 friends to take part in the challenge
3. Tag @ozivanutrition and #MyPCOSStory

#womenempowerment #womensupportingwomen #pcossupport
